00:56.347 --> 00:58.057
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>This is Tokyo...</i>

00:58.183 --> 01:00.768
<i>once a city of six million people.</i>

01:00.894 --> 01:02.978
<i>What has happened here</i>
<i>was caused by a force...</i>

01:03.104 --> 01:06.190
<i>which, up until a few days ago,</i>
<i>was entirely...</i>

01:06.316 --> 01:08.901
<i>beyond the scope</i>
<i>of man's imagination.</i>

01:09.027 --> 01:12.488
<i>Tokyo - a smoldering memorial</i>
<i>to the unknown...</i>

01:12.614 --> 01:15.449
<i>an unknown which,</i>
<i>at this very moment, still prevails...</i>

01:15.575 --> 01:19.078
<i>and could at any time lash out</i>
<i>with its terrible destruction...</i>

01:19.204 --> 01:21.789
<i>anywhere else in the world.</i>

01:21.915 --> 01:26.043
<i>There were once many people here</i>
<i>who could have told of what they saw.</i>

01:26.169 --> 01:28.045
<i>Now there are only a few.</i>

01:42.143 --> 01:44.186
<i>My name is Steve Martin.</i>

01:44.312 --> 01:48.232
<i>I'm a foreign correspondent</i>
<i>for</i> United World News.

01:48.399 --> 01:51.110
<i>I was headed</i>
<i>for an assignment in Cairo...</i>

01:51.236 --> 01:54.404
<i>when I stopped off in Tokyo</i>
<i>for a social call.</i>

01:54.572 --> 01:58.492
<i>But it turned out to be a visit</i>
<i>to the living hell of another world.</i>

02:23.601 --> 02:27.855
<i>Emergency hospitals were overflowing</i>
<i>with the maimed and the dead.</i>

02:27.981 --> 02:31.483
<i>For the living,</i>
<i>the horror of last night was over.</i>

02:31.609 --> 02:34.570
<i>The only thought left</i>
<i>was the paralyzing fear...</i>

02:34.696 --> 02:37.239
<i>that it could happen again today...</i>

02:37.365 --> 02:39.283
<i>or tomorrow.</i>

02:41.452 --> 02:43.370
[ Geiger Counter Clicking ]

02:45.039 --> 02:47.332
<i>Everyone who had survived</i>
<i>without serious injury...</i>

02:47.458 --> 02:49.918
<i>was helping to repair</i>
<i>the human wreckage.</i>

02:50.044 --> 02:52.462
<i>One of the survivors</i>
<i>was Emiko Yamane...</i>

02:52.630 --> 02:56.508
<i>the daughter of Japan's</i>
<i>famous paleontologist.</i>

02:56.634 --> 02:59.803
<i>For some of the victims,</i>
<i>there was hope.</i>

02:59.929 --> 03:02.806
<i>For others,</i>
<i>there would be no tomorrow.</i>

03:07.103 --> 03:09.229
[ Child Wailing ]

03:09.355 --> 03:11.315
<i>I don't know</i>
<i>how many hours went by...</i>

03:11.482 --> 03:14.818
<i>before an auxiliary</i>
<i>hospital unit found me.</i>

03:14.944 --> 03:16.987
<i>I knew it was daylight.</i>

03:17.155 --> 03:20.032
<i>I was surprised to be alive.</i>

03:21.075 --> 03:24.036
<i>The odor of scorched flesh</i>
<i>permeated the air.</i>

03:24.162 --> 03:26.038
<i>The sight of all the helpless</i>
<i>human wreckage...</i>

03:26.164 --> 03:28.332
<i>snapped me back to stark reality.</i>

03:28.499 --> 03:30.417
[ Wailing Continues ]

03:44.390 --> 03:46.600
[ Woman Sobbing ]

03:54.776 --> 03:56.944
Emiko. Emiko!

03:57.070 --> 03:59.696
Steve. Steve Martin.

03:59.864 --> 04:01.865
Are you badly hurt?

04:04.535 --> 04:07.454
After last night,
I'm lucky to be alive.

04:07.580 --> 04:10.082
I guess we're all living
on borrowed time.

04:10.208 --> 04:13.502
Oh, Steve,
what brought this upon us?

04:15.546 --> 04:17.547
I don't know, Emiko.

04:19.341 --> 04:21.009
I don't know.

04:27.600 --> 04:29.893
Your father - is he all right?

04:30.061 --> 04:34.314
Yes. He's meeting
with the security officials now.

04:37.110 --> 04:39.069
[ Groans ]

04:39.195 --> 04:41.071
Don't move, Steve.

04:41.239 --> 04:43.448
I'll try to get a doctor for you.

04:47.453 --> 04:49.746
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>It was still hard for me to believe...</i>

04:49.914 --> 04:53.208
<i>that I could be lying here</i>
<i>in a hospital alive....</i>

04:53.334 --> 04:55.752
<i>when I think of the thousands</i>
<i>of others dead and dying...</i>

04:55.878 --> 04:57.629
<i>in the ruins around me.</i>

04:57.755 --> 04:59.631
<i>When I think back,</i>
<i>only a few days ago...</i>

04:59.757 --> 05:01.717
<i>I was en route to Cairo...</i>

05:01.843 --> 05:04.594
<i>with a few days' layover in Tokyo.</i>

05:05.430 --> 05:09.933
<i>I was looking forward to a visit</i>
<i>with an old college friend, Dr. Serizawa...</i>

05:10.059 --> 05:13.770
<i>a theoretical scientist who was gaining</i>
<i>great recognition in the Far East...</i>

05:13.896 --> 05:16.148
<i>for his unusual experiments.</i>

05:18.818 --> 05:21.528
<i>While I was unaware</i>
<i>of it at the time...</i>

05:21.654 --> 05:25.657
<i>10,000 feet below,</i>
<i>an incident was about to take place...</i>

05:25.783 --> 05:29.202
<i>that would shake the foundations</i>
<i>of the civilized world.</i>

05:29.329 --> 05:31.872
dd [ Ballad ]

05:39.172 --> 05:42.132
<i>[ Explosions ]</i>

05:42.300 --> 05:44.217
[ Man Exclaims ]

05:46.888 --> 05:49.514
<i>- [ Men Clamoring ]</i>
<i>- [ Creature Bellowing ]</i>

05:50.808 --> 05:52.434
[ All Screaming ]

06:05.406 --> 06:07.324
[ Beeping Morse Code ]

06:19.128 --> 06:21.046
[ Morse Code Beeping ]

06:23.132 --> 06:25.467
DISTRESS FREQUENCY

06:33.559 --> 06:35.477
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] This morning,</i>
<i>it would have been impossible...</i>

06:35.603 --> 06:39.689
<i>for anyone to convince me that I would</i>
<i>ever see Tokyo like this again.</i>

06:50.743 --> 06:52.786
- Pardon. You are Mr. Steve Martin?
- Yes.

06:52.912 --> 06:55.288
I'm Shigeo Ioto,
assistant to Dr. Serizawa.

06:55.415 --> 06:57.916
Oh, how do you do?
And how is Serizawa?

06:58.042 --> 07:00.627
His health is fine, but he regrets
not being here to meet you.

07:00.753 --> 07:02.045
Something wrong?

07:02.171 --> 07:04.589
Dr. Serizawa had to go inland
on some field experiments.

07:04.715 --> 07:06.758
He wanted to delay them
until after your visit...

07:06.884 --> 07:08.718
but they were much too important.

07:08.886 --> 07:11.721
- He hopes that you understand.
- Of course.

07:11.848 --> 07:15.434
- Oh, when's he planning to return?
- Perhaps before your departure to Cairo.

07:15.560 --> 07:18.520
Meanwhile, if there's anything I can do,
please feel free to call me.

07:18.646 --> 07:20.188
I certainly will.

07:20.314 --> 07:22.941
[ Japanese ]

07:23.067 --> 07:25.026
[ Japanese ]

07:27.405 --> 07:29.239
I'm sorry, Mr. Martin,
but we must ask you...

07:29.407 --> 07:32.075
to come to the security office
for questioning.

07:32.201 --> 07:34.661
Is this a polite way
of telling me I'm under arrest?

07:34.787 --> 07:36.663
No, no arrest.
Just questioning.

07:36.789 --> 07:39.416
- But it is imperative that you come.
- Of course.

07:42.211 --> 07:44.045
I'll take your bag.
Hotel Mikasu?

07:44.172 --> 07:46.756
No. Still the Imperial.

07:46.924 --> 07:49.634
<i>[ Man Over P.A. ]</i>
<i>Flight 104 is arriving at ramp seven.</i>

07:54.390 --> 07:56.391
[ Japanese ]

07:58.436 --> 08:00.979
- How do you do, Mr. Martin?
- Mr. Iwanaga.

08:01.105 --> 08:04.107
During your flight last night,
did anything unusual occur?

08:05.443 --> 08:07.736
Well, I didn't notice anything.

08:07.862 --> 08:11.448
I was busy writing and reading,
and the rest of the time I was sleeping.

08:11.574 --> 08:13.158
Oh, I see.

08:13.284 --> 08:15.869
I understand you've questioned
everyone on my flight.

08:15.995 --> 08:17.871
What is it you're trying to find out?

08:17.997 --> 08:20.707
I represent <i>United World News.</i>

08:24.587 --> 08:26.630
I don't know, Mr. Martin.

08:31.052 --> 08:33.595
I don't know whether
it should be printed or not.

08:37.725 --> 08:39.934
I don't follow you.

08:40.061 --> 08:43.522
You see, we don't know
what it is we're dealing with.

08:43.648 --> 08:46.775
At 3:30 this morning,
a ship from Tokyo was literally wiped...

08:46.901 --> 08:49.778
from the surface of the ocean
in a matter of seconds.

08:50.947 --> 08:52.989
Anything from the ship's radio?

08:53.157 --> 08:55.992
It said there was
a blinding flash of light...

08:56.160 --> 08:58.453
and the ocean burst into flame.

09:00.081 --> 09:02.582
Could have been
a mine or a collision.

09:02.708 --> 09:06.586
Why would the radio men
not report a mine or a collision?

09:06.712 --> 09:09.005
That's a good point.

09:09.173 --> 09:11.675
Well, whatever's being done
I'd like to find out about.

09:11.842 --> 09:13.760
All right.
Come with me.

09:18.349 --> 09:18.390
<i>[ Man Speaking Japanese Over Radio ]</i>

09:18.391 --> 09:20.684
<i>[ Man Speaking Japanese Over Radio ]</i>

09:20.851 --> 09:22.769
<i>[ People Clamoring ]</i>

09:33.531 --> 09:36.408
<i>[ Radio Continues ]</i>

09:36.534 --> 09:39.202
This is the chart room
of the Nankai Steamship Company.

09:39.370 --> 09:41.746
It was their ship which was sunk.

09:41.872 --> 09:43.832
[ Japanese ]

09:51.549 --> 09:54.759
You mind telling me
what they're discussing?

09:54.885 --> 09:57.971
They're at a loss to explain how their ship
could disappear so suddenly.

09:58.097 --> 10:00.056
[ Japanese ]

10:03.978 --> 10:06.354
- Any survivors?
- No, not yet.

10:13.487 --> 10:16.406
They're in direct contact
with the rescue ship now.

10:16.532 --> 10:19.284
It should arrive at the scene
of the sinking in a few hours.

10:24.373 --> 10:26.875
[ Horn Blows ]

10:45.144 --> 10:47.187
[ Excited Chattering in Japanese ]

10:48.648 --> 10:51.441
Operator,
give me Paul, please. Rush.

10:51.609 --> 10:54.027
Paul?
[ Portuguese ]

11:01.077 --> 11:02.744
That's it, operator.

11:02.870 --> 11:05.997
Mr. George Lawrence,
<i>United World News</i> Chicago, U.S.A.

11:08.000 --> 11:11.002
‘‘Japanese ship disasters
puzzle world.

11:12.546 --> 11:14.464
Eight ships obliterated...

11:14.632 --> 11:17.759
by mysterious blinding flash of fire.

11:17.885 --> 11:20.637
No survivors found.

11:20.763 --> 11:24.641
Radio reports from stricken ships
gave same message."

11:25.726 --> 11:27.644
That's right.

11:27.812 --> 11:31.147
‘‘Terrible sea of fire engulfs all.

11:31.273 --> 11:36.111
Staggering death toll forces
all shipping schedules be canceled.

11:37.196 --> 11:40.824
Will remain Tokyo
unless word from you."

11:40.950 --> 11:42.867
Sign it ‘‘Steve Martin."

11:44.412 --> 11:46.079
You've got it. Thanks.

11:46.997 --> 11:49.332
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] Like a creeping illness,</i>
<i>panic began to spread...</i>

11:49.458 --> 11:51.209
<i>all over Japan.</i>

11:51.335 --> 11:54.504
<i>The Nankai Shipping Company</i>
<i>swarmed with distraught families...</i>

11:54.672 --> 11:56.673
<i>pleading for news of lost crews.</i>

11:56.841 --> 11:59.634
[ Japanese ]

12:04.932 --> 12:07.350
[ All Shouting ]

12:11.313 --> 12:13.523
[ Speaking Japanese ]

12:18.696 --> 12:20.780
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>The few survivors who had been found...</i>

12:20.906 --> 12:24.784
<i>died in a matter of minutes</i>
<i>from shock and strange burns.</i>

12:24.910 --> 12:26.870
<i>[ Morse Code Beeping ]</i>

12:34.086 --> 12:36.045
[ Crowd Clamoring ]

12:40.301 --> 12:42.510
[ Japanese ]

12:45.389 --> 12:48.016
<i>With disaster following disaster,</i>
<i>the terror-stricken people...</i>

12:48.142 --> 12:50.435
<i>demanded action be taken.</i>

12:50.561 --> 12:53.480
<i>Security officials and scientists</i>
<i>were called together.</i>

12:53.606 --> 12:56.733
<i>Dr. Yamane,</i>
<i>Japan's leading paleontologist...</i>

12:56.901 --> 12:59.486
<i>was among the top scientists</i>
<i>invited to the meeting.</i>

12:59.612 --> 13:03.656
<i>I had met Dr. Yamane through my friend</i>
<i>Serizawa several years ago.</i>

13:03.783 --> 13:08.578
<i>If there was to be an answer</i>
<i>to these mysterious ship disasters...</i>

13:08.704 --> 13:10.622
<i>it would come from these men.</i>

13:10.748 --> 13:12.707
[ Japanese ]

13:20.966 --> 13:23.927
<i>[ Man Speaking Japanese ]</i>

13:30.059 --> 13:31.976
[ Japanese ]

13:39.235 --> 13:42.111
I'm afraid my Japanese
is a little rusty.

13:42.279 --> 13:44.864
[ Japanese ]

13:44.990 --> 13:47.575
Dr. Yamane is suggesting
to the officials...

13:47.701 --> 13:50.954
that they question
the natives of a small island.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.456
He says that Odo Island
is close to the area...

13:53.624 --> 13:55.542
where the disasters
have taken place.

13:58.128 --> 13:59.921
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>Odo Island...</i>

14:00.047 --> 14:02.549
<i>a bleak spot of land in the Pacific...</i>

14:02.675 --> 14:04.634
<i>populated</i>
<i>with several hundred natives...</i>

14:04.760 --> 14:07.262
<i>who were now</i>
<i>half paralyzed with fear.</i>

14:14.687 --> 14:16.646
[ Japanese ]

14:39.378 --> 14:41.880
[ Murmuring Excitedly ]

14:46.176 --> 14:48.136
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>These people were the only ones...</i>

14:48.262 --> 14:50.471
<i>who had seen</i>
<i>some of the fires at sea.</i>

14:50.598 --> 14:53.975
<i>[ People Shouting ]</i>

14:54.101 --> 14:56.311
[ Chattering Excitedly ]

14:56.437 --> 14:58.521
[ Shouting In Japanese ]

14:59.857 --> 15:02.025
[ Chattering Excitedly ]

15:09.074 --> 15:13.453
<i>They were also the only ones</i>
<i>who saw a survivor of the sinkings...</i>

15:13.579 --> 15:15.538
<i>and his visit was a short one.</i>

15:15.706 --> 15:17.707
[ Shouting In Japanese ]

15:22.755 --> 15:25.298
[ Japanese ]

15:25.424 --> 15:27.425
[ Shouting ]

15:36.560 --> 15:38.728
<i>[ Aircraft Flying Overhead ]</i>

15:40.230 --> 15:43.983
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] The next morning,</i>
<i>a helicopter was dispatched from Tokyo.</i>

15:44.109 --> 15:47.737
<i>The security officer, Mr. Iwanaga,</i>
<i>had arranged for me to join...</i>

15:47.863 --> 15:51.407
<i>the group of officials who were</i>
<i>to question the natives of Odo Island.</i>

15:58.374 --> 16:00.249
<i>While various natives</i>
<i>of the island...</i>

16:00.376 --> 16:02.627
<i>were being interrogated</i>
<i>by the officials...</i>

16:02.753 --> 16:04.837
<i>Tomo and I went out</i>
<i>among the natives.</i>

16:04.964 --> 16:06.923
[ Japanese ]

16:23.774 --> 16:27.318
Hey, Tomo, we make him mad?

16:27.444 --> 16:30.113
He's frightened.
He's terribly frightened.

16:30.280 --> 16:32.156
He must've seen something.

16:32.282 --> 16:35.243
He claimed he saw a monster,
a horrible monster.

16:35.369 --> 16:37.453
If he saw a monster,
he's had too much sake.

16:37.621 --> 16:41.040
No, no, Mr. Martin.
These island people are very superstitious.

16:42.626 --> 16:44.752
Well, let's see what else
we can find out.

16:46.213 --> 16:49.215
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>It was decided that we'd spend the night...</i>

16:49.341 --> 16:53.302
<i>and it gave me an opportunity</i>
<i>to witness a rare ceremony...</i>

16:53.429 --> 16:55.722
<i>one that was all but forgotten.</i>

16:55.848 --> 16:58.474
<i>dd [ Native ]</i>

16:58.600 --> 17:01.686
The island people are beset
by many dangers, Steve -

17:01.812 --> 17:04.230
some real, some imagined.

17:04.356 --> 17:07.442
<i>This ceremony is dedicated</i>
<i>to one such danger.</i>

17:13.449 --> 17:15.657
<i>There's a legend</i>
<i>among the island people...</i>

17:15.784 --> 17:18.744
<i>that somewhere off their shores</i>
<i>there exists a monster...</i>

17:18.871 --> 17:21.664
too terrible
for a mortal to conceive.

17:21.790 --> 17:24.791
Many centuries ago, they used
to send a young girl out on a raft...

17:24.917 --> 17:27.211
each year as a sacrifice.

17:27.337 --> 17:29.297
<i>dd [ Continues ]</i>

17:38.515 --> 17:41.309
What's the name of this monster?

17:41.435 --> 17:44.520
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Godzilla. Godzilla!</i>

17:44.646 --> 17:46.606
[ Japanese ]

17:50.694 --> 17:53.321
Did you hear that? Godzilla.

17:57.367 --> 17:59.702
They believe their, uh, Godzilla...

17:59.870 --> 18:03.372
is responsible
for all these ship disasters?

18:04.374 --> 18:06.084
They're certain of it.

18:20.682 --> 18:23.017
<i>[ Wind Gusting ]</i>

18:31.568 --> 18:33.486
<i>[ Gusting Grows Louder ]</i>

18:37.741 --> 18:40.535
<i>[ Thunderous Pounding In Distance ]</i>

18:50.003 --> 18:51.921
<i>[ Pounding Grows Louder ]</i>

19:48.896 --> 19:51.439
[ Japanese ]

19:58.780 --> 20:01.157
<i>[ Boy Shouting In Japanese ]</i>

20:01.283 --> 20:03.201
[ Shouts ]

20:05.621 --> 20:09.415
<i>[ Creature Bellowing ]</i>

20:09.541 --> 20:11.709
<i>[ Thunderous Pounding ]</i>

20:16.840 --> 20:19.967
<i>[ Creature Bellowing ]</i>

20:24.348 --> 20:27.266
<i>[ Boy Shouting ]</i>

20:29.102 --> 20:32.688
[ All Shouting ]

20:54.211 --> 20:57.505
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>It was more than wind, rain, and lightning.</i>

20:57.631 --> 21:00.049
<i>Much more.</i>

21:00.217 --> 21:03.886
<i>I wasn't just sure what it was.</i>
<i>No one was sure.</i>

21:04.012 --> 21:07.431
<i>No one except the natives,</i>
<i>and they were positive.</i>

21:07.557 --> 21:10.601
<i>They said it was Godzilla.</i>

21:25.575 --> 21:28.661
<i>The next morning, the officials brought</i>
<i>some of the islanders back to Tokyo...</i>

21:28.787 --> 21:30.746
<i>to make a direct report.</i>

21:31.873 --> 21:34.041
[ Chattering In Japanese ]

21:42.134 --> 21:44.093
[ Japanese ]

21:54.229 --> 21:56.105
<i>Each of the natives of Odo Island...</i>

21:56.231 --> 21:58.816
<i>told his own story</i>
<i>of the sudden turbulence...</i>

21:58.942 --> 22:02.111
<i>and had his own ideas</i>
<i>of its cause.</i>

22:02.279 --> 22:05.323
<i>They were all of the opinion</i>
<i>that the destruction was brought about...</i>

22:05.449 --> 22:07.366
<i>by a living creature.</i>

22:07.492 --> 22:10.077
<i>[ Japanese Continues ]</i>

22:17.169 --> 22:19.128
[ Japanese ]

22:29.973 --> 22:32.600
I have not been
to the island myself...

22:32.726 --> 22:35.895
but the world today is filled
with many mysteries.

22:36.021 --> 22:39.815
In the Himalayas, footprints
of snowmen have been found.

22:39.983 --> 22:42.568
<i>No one knows</i>
<i>anything about them...</i>

22:42.694 --> 22:44.779
<i>so there's no one</i>
<i>who can explain</i>

22:44.905 --> 22:47.323
<i>a phenomenon</i>
<i>at the top of the world.</i>

22:47.449 --> 22:50.576
<i>Is it not possible that some other</i>
<i>unexplainable phenomenon....</i>

22:50.702 --> 22:53.079
<i>might exist at the bottom</i>
<i>of the ocean?</i>

22:53.205 --> 22:55.748
A research party should be
organized to make...

22:55.874 --> 22:58.542
a scientific survey of Odo Island.

22:58.668 --> 23:00.753
[ People Applauding ]

23:03.340 --> 23:06.050
I'm going to catch Dr. Yamane.
I'll see you later.

23:06.176 --> 23:09.053
It seems to me there are still
forces left in this world...

23:09.179 --> 23:11.055
that none of us can understand.

23:11.181 --> 23:12.890
[ Japanese ]

23:13.016 --> 23:15.017
Oh, excuse me.

23:15.185 --> 23:17.686
[ People Chattering ]

23:17.854 --> 23:21.107
- Dr. Yamane.
- Steve Martin. It is good to see you.

23:21.233 --> 23:24.443
You take this monster talk seriously?

23:24.569 --> 23:26.779
Who can tell?

23:26.905 --> 23:30.491
I understand you're heading
the research group to Odo Island.

23:30.617 --> 23:32.993
Yes. We leave this afternoon.

23:33.120 --> 23:36.747
With your permission, I'd like to come.
I've been cleared by the security office.

23:36.873 --> 23:39.750
Of course. Pier J at 2:00.

23:39.876 --> 23:42.169
Good. I'll see you then.

23:44.131 --> 23:47.007
- [ People Shouting ]
<i>- dd [ Brass Band ]</i>

23:47.134 --> 23:49.218
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>Pier J swarmed with well-wishers...</i>

23:49.386 --> 23:51.387
<i>for Dr. Yamane and his party.</i>

23:55.392 --> 23:57.435
<i>[ Shouting Continues ]</i>

23:58.728 --> 24:01.188
<i>[ Horn Blowing ]</i>

24:04.609 --> 24:06.569
[ Japanese ]

24:07.946 --> 24:11.824
<i>But there was still</i>
<i>a feeling of anxiety among us all...</i>

24:12.951 --> 24:15.578
<i>for every ship</i>
<i>that had taken this course...</i>

24:15.745 --> 24:17.872
<i>had vanished</i>
<i>from the face of the earth.</i>

24:22.711 --> 24:25.296
<i>Yes, there was a feeling of anxiety.</i>

24:26.590 --> 24:28.424
<i>But perhaps the two exceptions...</i>

24:28.592 --> 24:32.470
<i>were Emiko and a young</i>
<i>marine officer named Ogata.</i>

24:32.596 --> 24:35.931
<i>At the moment, they seemed</i>
<i>more interested in each other.</i>

24:36.099 --> 24:38.017
<i>When I'd last seen Emiko...</i>

24:38.143 --> 24:41.395
<i>she had just become engaged</i>
<i>to Dr. Serizawa.</i>

24:41.521 --> 24:43.856
<i>It was the usual triangle...</i>

24:43.982 --> 24:46.901
<i>only this time it was</i>
<i>to play an important part...</i>

24:47.027 --> 24:49.820
<i>in the lives of millions of people.</i>

24:49.946 --> 24:52.031
[ Japanese ]

25:49.214 --> 25:51.840
[ Geiger Counter Clicking ]

25:54.135 --> 25:57.263
This well is contaminated.
Please stay back.

25:57.389 --> 26:00.516
<i>- This ground is dangerous!</i>
- [ People Exclaiming ]

26:17.534 --> 26:19.451
Mr. Ojihara...

26:22.038 --> 26:24.290
these are footsteps
of a living creature.

26:24.416 --> 26:26.834
<i>[ Flashbulb Pops ]</i>

26:32.048 --> 26:33.882
[ Rapid Clicking ]

26:43.560 --> 26:45.728
They're also radioactive.

26:45.854 --> 26:49.607
This ground is dangerous!
Everybody, please stay back!

26:49.733 --> 26:51.692
[ Crowd Chattering ]

27:04.289 --> 27:06.206
Emiko...

27:06.333 --> 27:08.542
a trilobite, a three-ringed worm...

27:08.668 --> 27:10.794
which was thought to be extinct.

27:10.920 --> 27:13.130
Don't hold it in your bare hands!

27:16.676 --> 27:19.053
What does that mean?

27:19.179 --> 27:21.722
It's a fabulous discovery.

27:25.185 --> 27:27.603
Trilobite?

27:27.771 --> 27:29.897
- Isn't that a -
<i>- [ Bell Clanging ]</i>

27:32.275 --> 27:34.735
Godzilla!
[ Shouting, Indistinct ]

27:38.073 --> 27:39.948
What's that, Tomo?

27:40.075 --> 27:42.159
It's safer up on the hills.

27:48.750 --> 27:51.001
[ Panicked Shouting ]

27:51.127 --> 27:53.087
<i>[ Thunderous Pounding ]</i>

27:56.841 --> 27:58.801
<i>[ Clanging Continues ]</i>

28:10.397 --> 28:12.773
[ Japanese ]

28:17.987 --> 28:20.823
<i>[ Pounding Grows Louder ]</i>

28:23.076 --> 28:25.119
[ All Screaming ]

28:35.338 --> 28:37.798
[ Roaring ]

28:44.180 --> 28:47.182
- [ Screams ]
- [ Roaring ]

28:57.110 --> 28:58.736
[ Roaring ]

29:12.041 --> 29:14.835
<i>[ Pounding Fades ]</i>

29:19.758 --> 29:22.050
<i>[ Dr. Yamane ]</i>
<i>Emiko! Emiko!</i>

29:22.218 --> 29:25.262
- Emiko!
- [ Crowd Shouting ]

29:25.388 --> 29:28.515
- Emiko! Ogata!
- [ Panicked Chattering ]

29:28.641 --> 29:31.560
<i>[ Man Shouts in Japanese ]</i>

29:36.149 --> 29:38.442
[ Japanese ]

29:52.832 --> 29:55.209
Look at the size of those footprints!

29:59.798 --> 29:59.922
It can safely be assumed
that two million years ago...

29:59.923 --> 30:03.425
It can safely be assumed
that two million years ago...

30:03.593 --> 30:07.888
this brontosaurus and other
ancient reptiles roamed the earth.

30:08.014 --> 30:10.724
<i>It was known as the Jurassic age.</i>

30:12.018 --> 30:13.852
During this period,

30:13.978 --> 30:18.524
<i>there was another species which</i>
<i>we may call the intermediary animal...</i>

30:18.650 --> 30:22.569
<i>a cross between the land-living</i>
<i>and the sea-living animals.</i>

30:27.617 --> 30:30.661
Let us call this creature Godzilla...

30:30.787 --> 30:34.540
<i>according to the legend</i>
<i>of Odo Island.</i>

30:34.666 --> 30:37.543
And judging from this photograph...

30:37.669 --> 30:40.963
this creature is over 400 feet tall.

30:41.130 --> 30:43.006
[ All Murmuring ]

30:46.344 --> 30:49.096
[ Man Exclaiming In Japanese ]

30:57.856 --> 31:00.858
Of course,
the question we are...

31:00.984 --> 31:03.068
<i>asking ourselves is how this animal...</i>

31:03.194 --> 31:06.905
<i>happened to reappear</i>
<i>after all these centuries...</i>

31:07.031 --> 31:09.825
<i>and so near to the coast of Japan.</i>

31:09.951 --> 31:13.078
One answer could be that some
rare phenomenon of nature...

31:13.204 --> 31:17.541
allowed this breed
of the Jurassic age to reproduce itself...

31:17.667 --> 31:22.296
<i>and for a long span of time, it had</i>
<i>no reason to reappear to the world.</i>

31:22.422 --> 31:25.007
<i>But now that analysis</i>
<i>of radioactivity...</i>

31:25.133 --> 31:27.050
<i>of the creature's footprint...</i>

31:27.176 --> 31:30.554
<i>shows the existence of strontium 90...</i>

31:30.680 --> 31:33.390
<i>a product of the H-bomb...</i>

31:33.516 --> 31:37.811
<i>it is my belief that Godzilla</i>
<i>was resurrected...</i>

31:37.937 --> 31:41.648
due to the repeated
experiments of H-bombs.

31:41.774 --> 31:44.109
<i>[ People Murmuring ]</i>

31:45.945 --> 31:47.821
[ Speaking Japanese ]

31:47.947 --> 31:50.824
[ People Shouting ]

32:01.669 --> 32:04.004
- [ Man ] Hello?
- Can you hear me okay, George?

32:04.130 --> 32:05.839
[ George ]
You're comin' in clear.

32:05.965 --> 32:08.717
Now, let's have it, Steve.
What about this monster story of yours?

32:08.885 --> 32:12.095
Well, it's big and terrible...

32:12.221 --> 32:14.640
more frightening
than I ever thought possible.

32:14.766 --> 32:17.893
You realize your story's front-page
all over the country?

32:18.061 --> 32:20.354
We want to know
what's being done about this monster.

32:21.564 --> 32:24.066
Well, here's your headline:

32:24.233 --> 32:27.819
‘‘Security Decides to Use
Depth Bomb on Godzilla."

32:27.946 --> 32:29.613
Oh, that's fine.

32:29.739 --> 32:32.532
But how can they use depth bombs
against something they can't even see?

32:32.659 --> 32:36.244
Same way they look
for a submarine: sonar.

32:36.371 --> 32:38.372
Oh, they'll find him, all right.

32:38.498 --> 32:40.582
The big question is,
will they kill him?

32:41.918 --> 32:45.587
Well, stay on it, Steve,
and keep us posted.

32:45.755 --> 32:49.299
I will. So long, George.

33:09.195 --> 33:11.446
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

33:18.997 --> 33:22.958
- Hello?
- [ Speaking Japanese ]

33:23.126 --> 33:26.795
Steve, you are a better
newspaperman than a linguist.

33:26.963 --> 33:28.797
It is good to hear from you.

33:28.965 --> 33:32.217
I just got the message that you called.
Did you finish with your experiments?

33:32.343 --> 33:35.220
Yes, I finished.

33:35.346 --> 33:39.266
- Good. Let's have dinner tonight.
- Steve, make it tomorrow.

33:39.392 --> 33:42.811
Emiko is coming over this evening,
and she said it was important.

33:42.979 --> 33:46.231
- All right. I'll check with you tomorrow.
- That will be fine, Steve.

33:46.357 --> 33:48.316
<i>Sayonara.</i>

33:52.030 --> 33:54.489
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] The marriage</i>
<i>between Emiko and Dr. Serizawa...</i>

33:54.657 --> 33:56.658
<i>had been arranged</i>
<i>when they were both children.</i>

33:56.826 --> 33:59.161
<i>And while Emiko wasn't in love</i>
<i>with the great scientist...</i>

33:59.287 --> 34:02.039
<i>she had great respect</i>
<i>and admiration for him.</i>

34:02.165 --> 34:05.917
<i>It proved difficult for her to tell him</i>
<i>she was going to marry Ogata.</i>

34:06.044 --> 34:08.045
<i>- dd [ Radio ]</i>
- It...

34:08.170 --> 34:11.422
It's good to have you home,
Dr. Serizawa.

34:11.549 --> 34:13.800
It is good to be back, Emiko.

34:14.886 --> 34:17.304
I'm glad we have this time together.

34:18.889 --> 34:22.266
There is something important
I must tell you.

34:22.393 --> 34:24.436
[ Radio Switches Off ]

34:24.562 --> 34:27.481
But there is something far more
important which I must show you.

34:27.607 --> 34:28.815
Eh?

34:28.940 --> 34:30.817
<i>- Come with me.</i>
- [ Murmurs Agreement ]

34:52.590 --> 34:55.509
[ Machinery Humming, Clicking ]

35:02.225 --> 35:04.142
[ Exclaims ]

36:01.617 --> 36:03.743
[ Machine Whirring ]

36:07.039 --> 36:09.583
<i>Stand back!</i>

36:16.465 --> 36:18.425
[ Screams ]

36:39.488 --> 36:41.615
Emiko-san!

36:41.741 --> 36:43.742
The world must not know of this.

36:44.827 --> 36:47.245
Promise to keep my secret.

36:47.413 --> 36:49.164
[ Murmurs Agreement ]

36:49.290 --> 36:51.291
I won't even tell my father.

37:16.525 --> 37:18.818
What happened?

37:18.945 --> 37:20.820
Nothing.

37:20.947 --> 37:22.864
Nothing.

37:53.688 --> 37:56.106
[ Explosion ]

38:03.239 --> 38:05.198
[ Explosion ]

38:14.208 --> 38:16.126
<i>[ Explosions Continue ]</i>

38:42.778 --> 38:44.821
Father, what is it?

38:44.947 --> 38:47.449
They are so wrong.

38:47.616 --> 38:51.911
Godzilla should not be destroyed.
He should be studied.

38:52.038 --> 38:54.831
<i>Emiko...</i>

38:54.957 --> 38:58.084
<i>please, leave me alone.</i>

38:58.210 --> 39:00.128
<i>Hai.</i>

39:09.555 --> 39:12.182
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] By the end</i>
<i>of the day, it was generally assumed...</i>

39:12.308 --> 39:14.559
<i>that the underwater demolition</i>
<i>had ended...</i>

39:14.685 --> 39:17.062
<i>the short but terrible reign</i>
<i>of Godzilla.</i>

39:17.188 --> 39:20.648
<i>There was a feeling of relief</i>
<i>throughout Tokyo...</i>

39:20.816 --> 39:22.776
<i>even celebration.</i>

39:22.902 --> 39:26.321
<i>But both the hope</i>
<i>and celebration were short-lived.</i>

39:26.447 --> 39:28.615
<i>dd [ Tropical ]</i>

39:42.213 --> 39:44.672
<i>[ Thunderous Pounding ]</i>

39:52.556 --> 39:55.016
<i>- [ Woman Gasps ]</i>
- [ Roaring ]

39:55.184 --> 39:57.477
<i>[ People Screaming ]</i>

39:58.854 --> 40:00.438
Godzilla!

40:04.527 --> 40:07.445
<i>[ Screaming Continues ]</i>

40:07.571 --> 40:09.656
[ Panicked Shouting ]

40:20.709 --> 40:22.669
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>Within minutes, the city was aware...</i>

40:22.795 --> 40:25.130
<i>that Godzilla was inside Tokyo Harbor.</i>

40:25.256 --> 40:28.258
<i>Among the people,</i>
<i>there was a state of panic.</i>

40:32.304 --> 40:35.640
[ Japanese ]

40:35.766 --> 40:38.852
<i>The military used every man</i>
<i>and machine available...</i>

40:38.978 --> 40:42.397
<i>in an effort to stem</i>
<i>the oncoming terror.</i>

41:21.395 --> 41:23.813
- Has Emiko returned?
- <i>[ Emiko]</i> Hai.

41:37.912 --> 41:40.663
<i>- [ Klaxon Siren Sounds ]</i>
<i>- [ Thunderous Pounding ]</i>

41:44.627 --> 41:46.544
[ Japanese ]

41:58.641 --> 42:00.558
[ Emiko ]
Ogata-san!

42:03.103 --> 42:06.564
I couldn't tell Dr. Serizawa about us.

42:06.690 --> 42:08.566
I understand, Emiko.

42:08.692 --> 42:10.860
<i>[ Siren Winds Down ]</i>

42:12.112 --> 42:14.280
<i>[ Pounding Continues ]</i>

42:15.824 --> 42:18.618
[ Roaring ]

42:41.517 --> 42:43.685
<i>[ Sirens Wailing ]</i>

43:12.756 --> 43:14.757
Let's go up on the hill.

43:16.260 --> 43:18.219
[ Shouting In Japanese ]

43:44.622 --> 43:46.914
[ People Screaming ]

44:03.265 --> 44:06.601
[ People Laughing ]

44:19.782 --> 44:22.116
<i>[ People Screaming ]</i>

44:51.522 --> 44:53.481
[ Screaming, Shouting ]

45:26.390 --> 45:29.642
<i>- [ Man ] He's leaving!</i>
- [ Roaring ]

45:29.768 --> 45:32.478
<i>[ Man #2 ]</i>
<i>But he will be back.</i>

45:35.607 --> 45:37.775
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>The damage had been severe...</i>

45:37.901 --> 45:40.820
<i>but fortunately confined</i>
<i>to the dock section of the city.</i>

45:40.946 --> 45:42.864
<i>Godzilla was still in Tokyo Bay...</i>

45:42.990 --> 45:45.575
<i>and there was every reason</i>
<i>to believe he would return...</i>

45:45.701 --> 45:48.035
<i>unless some means</i>
<i>was found to stop him.</i>

45:48.203 --> 45:50.913
[ Japanese ]

46:02.176 --> 46:03.801
Steve.

46:03.927 --> 46:05.803
- Hey, Steve.
- Hi, Tomo.

46:05.929 --> 46:09.223
- What did you run out of the meeting for?
- Got to get this story off to the paper.

46:09.349 --> 46:11.559
- Anything happen after I left?
- Yes.

46:11.685 --> 46:14.270
They're making one last
big effort to stop him.

46:14.396 --> 46:16.814
- And what's that?
- Come here. I'll show you.

46:23.071 --> 46:26.908
<i>Tokyo is surrounded</i>
<i>by high-tension electrical towers.</i>

46:28.076 --> 46:30.286
<i>To get to the heart of the city...</i>

46:30.412 --> 46:35.166
<i>Godzilla would have to break through</i>
<i>300,000 volts of electricity.</i>

46:35.292 --> 46:39.253
The officials are trying to have
everything ready by nightfall.

46:42.758 --> 46:45.635
Now I must report back
to my station.

46:45.761 --> 46:47.970
All right.
And thanks, Tomo.

46:48.096 --> 46:50.139
- So long, Steve.
<i>- Sayonara.</i>

46:53.310 --> 46:56.395
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] The security officials</i>
<i>ordered a general evacuation...</i>

46:56.522 --> 46:59.065
<i>of all nonessential personnel.</i>

46:59.191 --> 47:02.735
<i>It was a monumental job,</i>
<i>but a job which had to be done.</i>

47:02.861 --> 47:05.905
[ Panicked Shouting ]

47:16.792 --> 47:19.752
<i>[ Man Over P.A. In Japanese ]</i>

47:33.684 --> 47:36.435
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] By nightfall,</i>
<i>everyone was off the streets.</i>

47:41.650 --> 47:44.277
<i>The news office commanded</i>
<i>a good view of Tokyo...</i>

47:44.403 --> 47:48.197
<i>and was receiving all reports</i>
<i>directly from security headquarters.</i>

48:10.846 --> 48:13.556
This tape recording
is for George Lawrence...

48:13.682 --> 48:16.350
<i>United World News,</i>
Chicago, U.S.A.

48:21.023 --> 48:21.063
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] Everyone remaining</i>
<i>in the city was on a watch-and-wait basis.</i>

48:21.064 --> 48:25.109
<i>[ Steve Narrating ] Everyone remaining</i>
<i>in the city was on a watch-and-wait basis.</i>

48:26.278 --> 48:29.780
<i>The wait was not a long one.</i>

48:59.645 --> 49:04.190
George, here in Tokyo, time has been
turned back two million years.

49:04.316 --> 49:07.234
This is my report as it happens.

49:07.402 --> 49:10.321
A prehistoric monster
the Japanese call Godzilla...

49:10.447 --> 49:12.865
has just walked out of Tokyo Bay.

49:12.991 --> 49:16.535
<i>He's as tall as a 30-story building.</i>

49:18.914 --> 49:22.792
And now he's making his way
toward the city's main line of defense:

49:22.918 --> 49:27.463
<i>300,000 volts of electricity</i>
<i>strung around the city as a barrier...</i>

49:27.589 --> 49:30.049
<i>a barrier against Godzilla.</i>

49:39.768 --> 49:41.352
[ Buzzer Sounds ]

49:41.478 --> 49:44.313
[ Roaring ]

50:07.004 --> 50:09.255
[ Roaring ]

50:36.408 --> 50:40.161
I can hardly believe
what has just happened.

50:40.287 --> 50:42.621
Now it seems Tokyo has no defense.

50:45.333 --> 50:47.251
[ Roaring ]

50:52.215 --> 50:55.593
[ Panicked Shouting ]

51:42.766 --> 51:44.725
[ Screaming ]

51:54.152 --> 51:56.570
[ Sirens Wailing ]

52:34.484 --> 52:39.113
<i>They're moving an entire tank corps</i>
<i>to point-blank firing range.</i>

52:39.281 --> 52:43.576
I'm saying a prayer, George -
a prayer for the whole world.

53:34.002 --> 53:37.463
George, the tanks have been
wiped out by a wall of flames.

53:38.757 --> 53:41.717
Neither man nor his machines
are able to stop this creature.

53:43.345 --> 53:45.596
[ Screaming ]

53:50.685 --> 53:53.187
[ Japanese ]

53:54.522 --> 53:57.358
<i>[ Japanese Continues Over Radio ]</i>

54:05.909 --> 54:07.910
[ Roaring ]

54:09.537 --> 54:11.664
[ Shouts In Japanese ]

54:15.335 --> 54:17.294
[ Man Screams ]

54:17.420 --> 54:19.880
[ Panicked Shouting ]

54:41.987 --> 54:44.405
[ Shouting Continues ]

55:10.849 --> 55:12.891
[ Roaring ]

55:50.388 --> 55:54.266
Godzilla has turned
the heart of Tokyo into a sea of fire.

55:54.392 --> 55:58.145
<i>Beneath the flames,</i>
<i>thousands lie dead or dying.</i>

56:16.081 --> 56:19.124
[ Tolling ]

56:35.683 --> 56:37.601
[ Japanese ]

56:39.562 --> 56:42.898
[ Roaring ]

57:04.212 --> 57:06.964
[ Screaming ]

57:14.264 --> 57:16.723
Nothing can save the city now.

57:24.941 --> 57:27.401
[ Roaring ]

57:33.992 --> 57:36.618
<i>[ Man Over P.A. In Japanese ]</i>

57:40.957 --> 57:43.292
<i>[ Rumbling, Crashing ]</i>

57:53.136 --> 57:55.012
<i>[ Man On P.A. Continues ]</i>

58:03.313 --> 58:06.356
- This is it, George.
- [ Roaring ]

58:06.483 --> 58:09.318
Steve Martin
signing off from Tokyo, Japan.

58:37.138 --> 58:40.516
[ Roaring ]

58:49.150 --> 58:51.610
[ Japanese ]

59:02.830 --> 59:06.083
- [ Announcer Speaking Japanese ]
- [ Godzilla Roaring ]

59:35.822 --> 59:37.739
[ Japanese ]

01:00:14.235 --> 01:00:17.237
[ Shouting, Cheering ]

01:01:19.842 --> 01:01:22.260
[ Woman Screaming ]

01:01:25.556 --> 01:01:27.641
[ Screaming Continues ]

01:01:30.728 --> 01:01:32.688
[ Woman Sobbing ]

01:01:41.572 --> 01:01:43.490
Watch it!

01:01:57.463 --> 01:01:59.506
Hi, Emiko.

01:01:59.632 --> 01:02:01.591
You've been sleeping very nervously.

01:02:01.718 --> 01:02:05.387
- Hello, Ogata.
- Hello, Steve.

01:02:08.725 --> 01:02:10.600
Anything new develop?

01:02:10.727 --> 01:02:12.644
<i>[ Emiko ]</i>
<i>Nothing new will develop unless -</i>

01:02:12.770 --> 01:02:15.939
- [ Ogata ] Unless what?
- I was shown a terrible secret...

01:02:16.065 --> 01:02:19.317
which is probably the only weapon
which could destroy Godzilla.

01:02:19.444 --> 01:02:22.571
<i>- What is it?</i>
- I promised Dr. Serizawa...

01:02:22.697 --> 01:02:26.199
<i>never to reveal his secret to anyone.</i>

01:02:26.367 --> 01:02:28.910
Emiko...

01:02:29.036 --> 01:02:32.831
Emiko, last night
Tokyo was destroyed.

01:02:32.957 --> 01:02:36.585
Tomorrow it might be
Osaka or Yokohama.

01:02:36.711 --> 01:02:38.587
If you can help, you must.

01:02:38.713 --> 01:02:41.006
<i>[ Emiko ]</i>
<i>When I went to see Dr. Serizawa...</i>

01:02:41.132 --> 01:02:44.134
I had intended to tell him
about Ogata and me...

01:02:44.260 --> 01:02:46.762
<i>but there was something</i>
<i>he wanted to show me first.</i>

01:02:53.311 --> 01:02:55.228
[ Japanese ]

01:03:17.627 --> 01:03:19.753
[ Screams ]

01:03:30.640 --> 01:03:33.600
<i>[ Emiko ] Dr. Serizawa had been</i>
<i>experimenting with oxygen...</i>

01:03:33.768 --> 01:03:37.103
<i>when he came upon</i>
<i>a terrible chemical discovery -</i>

01:03:37.271 --> 01:03:39.981
<i>a way to destroy</i>
<i>all oxygen in water...</i>

01:03:40.107 --> 01:03:42.984
<i>thereby disintegrating</i>
<i>all living matter.</i>

01:03:43.110 --> 01:03:45.403
<i>An amount no larger</i>
<i>than a baseball...</i>

01:03:45.530 --> 01:03:49.115
<i>could turn Tokyo Bay</i>
<i>into a graveyard.</i>

01:03:49.283 --> 01:03:53.370
<i>Serizawa had found</i>
<i>a terrible destructive power...</i>

01:03:53.496 --> 01:03:55.872
<i>and until he could find</i>
<i>a counteracting good...</i>

01:03:55.998 --> 01:03:57.874
<i>that would come</i>
<i>from this discovery...</i>

01:03:58.000 --> 01:04:00.961
<i>he didn't want the world</i>
<i>to know his secret.</i>

01:04:01.087 --> 01:04:03.255
[ Japanese ]

01:04:08.344 --> 01:04:10.303
<i>[ Liquid Bubbling ]</i>

01:04:20.731 --> 01:04:24.109
<i>He made me promise</i>
<i>never to tell what I had seen.</i>

01:04:24.235 --> 01:04:26.695
<i>[ Ogata ]</i>
<i>Emiko, we need Serizawa's help.</i>

01:04:26.821 --> 01:04:28.864
There's no other way.

01:04:28.990 --> 01:04:31.157
If I could only see him...

01:04:31.325 --> 01:04:33.243
just talk to him.

01:04:34.412 --> 01:04:37.706
Perhaps I can change his mind.
Ogata will go with me.

01:04:37.832 --> 01:04:41.626
Whatever you do, Emiko,
you mustn't fail.

01:05:01.272 --> 01:05:03.231
<i>[ Ogata ]</i>
<i>Serizawa-san.</i>

01:05:08.029 --> 01:05:09.946
Sit down.

01:05:14.118 --> 01:05:18.038
Doctor, I know of
your Oxygen Destroyer.

01:05:18.205 --> 01:05:22.500
<i>- We must have it.</i>
- I don't know what you are talking about!

01:05:26.714 --> 01:05:28.506
<i>I broke my promise, Serizawa.</i>

01:05:28.633 --> 01:05:31.635
I told Steve Martin and Ogata.

01:05:31.761 --> 01:05:33.637
<i>They both agree.</i>

01:05:33.763 --> 01:05:37.599
You must use your Oxygen Destroyer
against Godzilla. [ Sobbing ]

01:05:41.771 --> 01:05:45.899
- No.
<i>- [ Ogata ] Serizawa-san!</i>

01:05:50.696 --> 01:05:52.697
Serizawa-san!

01:05:54.075 --> 01:05:56.826
- Ah, Serizawa-san!
<i>- Let go!</i>

01:05:56.953 --> 01:05:59.704
- We must have the formula! We must!
- Let go!

01:05:59.830 --> 01:06:02.082
Please stop!

01:06:02.249 --> 01:06:04.334
<i>- [ Men Shouting ]</i>
<i>- [ Glass Clattering ]</i>

01:06:04.460 --> 01:06:06.753
<i>[ Emiko Screams ]</i>

01:06:06.879 --> 01:06:08.838
<i>[ Ogata ]</i>
<i>Serizawa-san!</i>

01:06:12.468 --> 01:06:14.761
Ogata-san!

01:06:14.929 --> 01:06:16.846
[ Serizawa ]
Ogata-san!

01:06:43.457 --> 01:06:45.458
Sorry, Ogata.

01:06:47.378 --> 01:06:50.046
The Oxygen Destroyer
cannot be used.

01:06:55.136 --> 01:06:57.387
If we don't defend ourselves
from Godzilla now...

01:06:57.513 --> 01:06:59.472
<i>what will become of us?</i>

01:06:59.598 --> 01:07:02.183
And what will become of us
if a weapon such as I now have...

01:07:02.309 --> 01:07:04.436
<i>falls into the wrong hands?</i>

01:07:13.863 --> 01:07:16.865
Then you have a responsibility
no man has ever faced.

01:07:16.991 --> 01:07:20.660
<i>You have your fear,</i>
<i>which might become reality...</i>

01:07:20.786 --> 01:07:23.705
and you have Godzilla,
which <i>is</i> reality.

01:07:26.333 --> 01:07:28.293
[ Gasps ]

01:07:38.220 --> 01:07:41.931
<i>[ Man On TV ] Attention.</i>
<i>Attention, people of Japan.</i>

01:07:42.058 --> 01:07:44.726
<i>At this moment,</i>
<i>a nationwide prayer...</i>

01:07:44.852 --> 01:07:49.022
<i>is being observed for the survivors</i>
<i>of devastated Tokyo.</i>

01:07:49.148 --> 01:07:52.358
<i>The voices of our children</i>
<i>are raised in a prayer...</i>

01:07:52.526 --> 01:07:55.695
<i>for the courage to surmount</i>
<i>the destruction of today...</i>

01:07:55.863 --> 01:07:58.198
and look forward with hope...

01:07:58.324 --> 01:08:00.575
for peace and light.

01:08:00.701 --> 01:08:03.369
dd [ Girls' Choir: Japanese ]

01:08:17.093 --> 01:08:19.426
<i>dd [ Continues ]</i>

01:08:36.569 --> 01:08:38.488
dd [ Continues ]

01:08:43.577 --> 01:08:45.495
dd [ Continues ]

01:09:33.002 --> 01:09:34.961
dd [ Continues ]

01:09:46.140 --> 01:09:48.057
<i>dd [ Continues ]</i>

01:10:01.488 --> 01:10:03.531
<i>[ TV Switches Off ]</i>

01:10:06.160 --> 01:10:08.745
Have you decided?

01:10:08.871 --> 01:10:11.915
Yes. But this must be
the only time...

01:10:12.041 --> 01:10:14.125
<i>the Oxygen Destroyer</i>
<i>will be used.</i>

01:10:46.533 --> 01:10:48.952
[ Sobbing ]

01:11:07.805 --> 01:11:09.889
- [ Geiger Counter Clicking ]
<i>- [ Steve Narrating ] The boat...</i>

01:11:10.057 --> 01:11:12.684
<i>finding the location of Godzilla...</i>

01:11:12.810 --> 01:11:15.478
<i>the Oxygen Destroyer -</i>

01:11:18.440 --> 01:11:21.317
<i>all these have been accomplished.</i>

01:11:21.443 --> 01:11:25.571
<i>Serizawa insisted upon helping</i>
<i>Ogata place the weapon.</i>

01:11:32.579 --> 01:11:36.040
[ Man ]
And now the divers are descending.

01:11:36.166 --> 01:11:38.751
<i>We ask the whole world</i>
<i>to stand by.</i>

01:12:18.042 --> 01:12:20.418
They have reached the bottom.

01:14:00.310 --> 01:14:02.270
[ Shouting In Japanese ]

01:14:39.141 --> 01:14:43.728
<i>Serizawa!</i>
<i>Serizawa! Serizawa!</i>

01:14:45.314 --> 01:14:47.732
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>One diver is up. It is Ogata.</i>

01:14:47.858 --> 01:14:51.444
<i>Dr. Serizawa has not yet</i>
<i>started his ascent.</i>

01:14:57.117 --> 01:14:59.535
[ Excited Chattering ]

01:15:34.112 --> 01:15:36.113
<i>[ Water Churning Loudly ]</i>

01:16:01.306 --> 01:16:03.182
Serizawa! Serizawa-san!

01:16:03.350 --> 01:16:05.935
<i>[ Japanese ]</i>

01:16:06.061 --> 01:16:07.770
Serizawa-san!

01:16:19.866 --> 01:16:22.952
Ogata, it is working!

01:16:24.246 --> 01:16:26.831
Live happily with Emiko.
Good-bye.

01:16:31.628 --> 01:16:34.005
Serizawa!
Pull the line up!

01:16:34.131 --> 01:16:35.798
<i>Answer me! Serizawa!</i>

01:17:02.284 --> 01:17:04.076
Serizawa!

01:17:20.135 --> 01:17:22.345
[ Bellowing ]

01:18:18.151 --> 01:18:20.986
<i>[ People Murmuring ]</i>

01:18:23.198 --> 01:18:26.242
People of the world,
Godzilla is dead.

01:18:26.368 --> 01:18:29.995
<i>Give us strength to rebuild</i>
<i>our beloved land.</i>

01:18:30.163 --> 01:18:32.123
[ Weeping ]

01:18:39.297 --> 01:18:41.674
He said, ‘‘Be happy together."

01:18:44.678 --> 01:18:46.637
[ Sobbing ]

01:19:01.987 --> 01:19:04.196
<i>[ Steve Narrating ]</i>
<i>The menace was gone.</i>

01:19:04.364 --> 01:19:06.991
<i>So was a great man.</i>

01:19:08.785 --> 01:19:11.954
<i>But the whole world</i>
<i>could wake up and live again.</i>

01:19:58.251 --> 01:20:00.252
<i>[ Thunderous Pounding ]</i>

